{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.7",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 7,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 7",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 7 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:1",
      "text": "Is not the life of man upon earth a state of trial? and his existence as that of a hireling by the day?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:2",
      "text": "Or as a servant that fears his master, and one who has grasped a shadow? or as a hireling waiting for his pay?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:3",
      "text": "So have I also endured months of vanity, and nights of pain have been appointed me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:4",
      "text": "Whenever I lie down, I say, When will it be day? and whenever I rise up, again I say when will it be evening? and I am full of pains from evening to morning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:5",
      "text": "And my body is covered with loathsome worms; and I waste away, scraping off clods of dust from my eruption.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:6",
      "text": "And my life is lighter than a word, and has perished in vain hope.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:7",
      "text": "Remember then that my life is breath, and mine eye shall not yet again see good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:8",
      "text": "The eye of him that sees me shall not see me again: thine eyes are upon me, and I am no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:9",
      "text": "I am as a cloud that is cleared away from the sky: for if a man go down to the grave, he shall not come up again:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:10",
      "text": "and he shall surely not return to his own house, neither shall his place know him any more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:11",
      "text": "Then neither will I refrain my mouth: I will speak being in distress; being in anguish I will disclose the bitterness of my soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:12",
      "text": "Am I a sea, or a serpent, that thou hast set a watch over me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:13",
      "text": "I said that my bed should comfort me, and I would privately counsel with myself on my couch.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:14",
      "text": "Thou scarest me with dreams, and dost terrify me with visions.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:15",
      "text": "Thou wilt separate life from my spirit; and yet keep my bones from death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:16",
      "text": "For I shall not live for ever, that I should patiently endure: depart from me, for my life is vain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:17",
      "text": "For what is man, that thou hast magnified him? or that thou givest heed to him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:18",
      "text": "Wilt thou visit him till the morning, and judge him till the time of rest?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:19",
      "text": "How long dost thou not let me alone, nor let me go, until I shall swallow down my spittle?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:20",
      "text": "If I have sinned, what shall I be able to do, O thou that understandest the mind of men? why hast thou made me as thine accuser, and why am I a burden to thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.7.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:21",
      "text": "Why hast thou not forgotten my iniquity, and purged my sin? but now I shall depart to the earth; and in the morning, I am no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
